The husband and work partner of a Japanese reporter who was killed in Syria has told how his wife was shot dead moments after they were ambushed by government troops.

Mika Yamamoto, 45, an award-winning journalist, was gunned down last month in the flashpoint city of Aleppo on her first day in the country.

Her husband, photographer Kazutaka Sato, who was with her at the time, described how they fled in panic after the soldiers opened fire.

