He added: 'I think it was her firm belief that you can stop a war with journalism ... she would also turn her attention to children.

'I believe she wanted to tell the world how they are hurt, dead and bruised in their hearts.'

Mr Sato said the only way he believes he can come to terms with what happened is to find out exactly what happened.

